the dom is a way to represent a web page so that programs like js can interact with it 

A browser takes your HTML documenmt and turns it into the DOM


//accessing by CSS selectors
   i: Single element 
   Method: documentt.querySelector(selector)
   Description: Return the first element matching the specified CSS selector

  ii: Multiple Elements:
  Method : document,querySelectorAll(selector)
  Description: Return a static nodelist of all elements matching the specified CSS selector.


  iii: //Accesing by tag name 
  Method :  document.getElementsByTagName(tagName) ;
  Description : Return a live Html collection of all elemens with the specified tag name (eg.   ,div ,a , p ..etc)

  iv: Accesing using relationship 
  a. Parent node 
  Method: element.parentNode or element.parentElement
  Description: Access the immediate parewnt of an element . 

  b. Child Node 
  Method: element.childNode (include textNode) or element.children(only element nodes)
  Description: Acces all child nodes of an element . 
  c. sibling Nodes

 